<section class="calloutBox">
  <h2>What Most Gardeners Should Actually Use</h2>

  <p>
    For most tomato plants producing heavy fruit, use a soft, adjustable truss sling placed under the cluster before it becomes stressed. Attach it to your existing support system and adjust it so the fruit weight is partially lifted.
  </p>

  <p>
    You do not need to support every truss. Focus on the largest or most vulnerable clusters where breakage is most likely.
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
    Support the fruit early, and you avoid losing it later.
  </p>
</section>

